sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Client
    participant Server

    Note over Client,Server: Phase 1: Negotiation
    Client->>Server: Client Hello (Supported Ciphers, Client Random)
    Server->>Client: Server Hello (Chosen Cipher, Server Random)
    
    Note over Client,Server: Phase 2: Authentication
    Server->>Client: Certificate (Server's Public Key + CA Signature)
    Server->>Client: Server Hello Done
    
    Note over Client: Client verifies CA Signature
    
    Note over Client,Server: Phase 3: Key Exchange
    Note over Client: Client generates Pre-Master Secret
    Note over Client: Encrypts Secret with Server's Public Key
    Client->>Server: Client Key Exchange (Encrypted Pre-Master Secret)
    
    Note over Server: Server decrypts Secret with its Private Key
    
    Note over Client,Server: Both independently calculate Symmetric Session Key
    
    Note over Client,Server: Phase 4: Secure Tunnel Established
    Client->>Server: Change Cipher Spec (Ready to encrypt)
    Client->>Server: Finished (Encrypted handshake verification)
    Server->>Client: Change Cipher Spec (Ready to encrypt)
    Server->>Client: Finished (Encrypted handshake verification)
    
    Note over Client,Server: Application Data flows using Symmetric Session Key
    rect rgb(200, 255, 200)
    Client<<-->>Server: Encrypted HTTP Traffic
    end
